  m_text: Activity Diagram is actually defined as the change of state of the objects.
    The solution description of the system is completed by the behavior model. The
    behavior model consists of the aspects activities and states. Activities are
    defined for each state.  In order for a state to be viewed, predefined events
    must occur which includes the states and division into partial models and detailed
    functionality of the system for various states.
